---
import { Image } from "astro:assets";
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
import logoUrl from "../assets/grompack_logo.png";
---

<Layout title="GromPack | User Manual">
  <header class="navbar">
    <nav>
      <a href="/"
        ><img src={logoUrl.src} alt="GromPack Logo" class="nav-logo" /></a
      >
      <ul>
        <li><a href="/">Product</a></li>
        <li><a href="/manual" class="active">Manual</a></li>
      </ul>
    </nav>
  </header>

  <main class="manual-container">
    <aside class="sidebar">
      <h3>Contents</h3>
      <ul>
        <li><a href="#section-1">1. Initialization</a></li>
        <li><a href="#section-2">2. Mounting Protocol</a></li>
        <li><a href="#section-3">3. Data Acquisition</a></li>
        <li><a href="#section-4">4. Power Management</a></li>
      </ul>
    </aside>

    <article class="manual-content">
      <h1>GromPack Operations Manual</h1>
      <p class="subtitle">Version 1.0.4 | System Architecture: nRF54L15</p>

      <section id="section-1">
        <h2>1. Initialization</h2>
        <p>
          Before deployment, the GromPack telemetry module must be paired and
          initialized via the host application to ensure a synchronized clock
          and active logging state.
        </p>
        <ol>
          <li>
            Connect the module to the programming jig via the 4-pin SWD
            interface.
          </li>
          <li>
            Flash the latest Zephyr RTOS binary using a standard J-Link
            programmer.
          </li>
          <li>
            Verify the initialization sequence: The onboard micro-LED will pulse
            rapidly for 3 seconds upon a successful boot.
          </li>
        </ol>
      </section>

      <section id="section-2">
        <h2>2. Mounting Protocol</h2>
        <p>
          Proper mounting is critical to minimize behavioral interference in the
          test subject while maintaining optimal antenna orientation.
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>
            <strong>Surface Preparation:</strong> Ensure the dorsal surface is clean
            and dry.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Adhesion:</strong> Apply a microscopic drop of bio-compatible
            UV-curing epoxy to the underside of the GromPack PCB.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Placement:</strong> Position the device centrally on the thorax.
            Expose to 365nm UV light for 10 seconds to secure the bond.
          </li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section id="section-3">
        <h2>3. Data Acquisition</h2>
        <p>
          The module streams high-resolution accelerometer and orientation data.
          Ensure line-of-sight to the base station for optimal continuous
          streaming.
        </p>
        <div class="note-box">
          <strong>Note:</strong> If the connection is lost, GromPack automatically
          falls back to local flash storage until the link is re-established.
        </div>
      </section>
    </article>
  </main>
</Layout>

<style is:global>
  /* Keep the Base Styles and Navbar styles from the index.astro here, 
    or move them to a global CSS file or Layout component.
  */
  :root {
    --bg: #f5f5f7;
    --text-primary: #1d1d1f;
    --text-secondary: #86868b;
    --border: #d2d2d7;
  }

  body {
    background-color: var(--bg);
    color: var(--text-primary);
    font-family:
      -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, "Segoe UI", Roboto, sans-serif;
    margin: 0;
    -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased;
  }

  .navbar {
    /* ... same as index.astro ... */
  }
  .navbar nav {
    display: flex;
    justify-content: space-between;
    align-items: center;
    max-width: 1200px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 15px 40px;
  }
  .nav-logo {
    height: 30px;
  }
  .navbar ul {
    display: flex;
    gap: 30px;
    list-style: none;
    margin: 0;
    padding: 0;
  }
  .navbar a {
    text-decoration: none;
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    font-weight: 500;
  }
  .navbar a.active {
    color: var(--text-primary);
  }

  /* Manual Specific Layout */
  .manual-container {
    display: flex;
    max-width: 1000px;
    margin: 120px auto 100px;
    padding: 0 40px;
    gap: 60px;
  }

  /* Sidebar styling */
  .sidebar {
    width: 200px;
    flex-shrink: 0;
    position: sticky;
    top: 100px; /* Sticks slightly below the navbar */
    height: fit-content;
  }

  .sidebar h3 {
    font-size: 14px;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 1px;
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    margin-bottom: 20px;
  }
  .sidebar ul {
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
    margin: 0;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 15px;
  }
  .sidebar a {
    text-decoration: none;
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    font-size: 15px;
    transition: color 0.2s ease;
  }
  .sidebar a:hover {
    color: var(--text-primary);
  }

  /* Main Content styling */
  .manual-content {
    flex-grow: 1;
    background: white;
    padding: 60px 80px;
    border-radius: 24px;
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    box-shadow: 0 4px 20px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.02);
  }

  .manual-content h1 {
    font-size: 40px;
    margin-bottom: 5px;
  }
  .subtitle {
    font-family: monospace;
    font-size: 14px;
    margin-bottom: 50px;
    color: var(--text-secondary);
  }

  .manual-content section {
    margin-bottom: 60px;
  }
  .manual-content h2 {
    font-size: 24px;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
    padding-bottom: 10px;
    margin-bottom: 20px;
  }

  .manual-content p,
  .manual-content li {
    font-size: 16px;
    line-height: 1.7;
    color: #333;
    margin-bottom: 15px;
  }
  .manual-content ol,
  .manual-content ul {
    padding-left: 20px;
    margin-bottom: 20px;
  }
  .manual-content li {
    margin-bottom: 10px;
  }

  .note-box {
    background-color: var(--bg);
    padding: 20px;
    border-radius: 12px;
    border-left: 4px solid var(--text-primary);
    font-size: 15px;
    color: var(--text-primary);
  }
</style>
